 kidneys with increased\\Nechogenicity, reflecting interstitial edema","guid":"vu3zmbeb5FZXy_84HHtPhw","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"129","parent":"79","text":"\\\\*Renal\\Nbiopsy\\\\*","guid":"5gHXIvCLM1gEyZ6Lh-delA","children":[{"id":"130","parent":"129","text":"\\\\*Indications\\Ninclude\\\\*","guid":"LBY3PCt-0X_g2qof-WN6LQ","children":[{"id":"131","parent":"130","text":"No improvement or the patient worsens after 3–5 days of\\Nsupportive care and withdrawal of potential causative agent.","guid":"InLeWBzEcXUOQvu_WFq3-Q","children":[]},{"id":"132","parent":"130","text":"Guiding treatment of suspected causes","guid":"NJ3BEDZwjF2LiK9hvcuBoA","children":[]}]},{"id":"133","parent":"129","text":"\\\\*Findings\\\\*","guid":"r6D_p1QK-VLJbseZXyfrMA","children":[{"id":"134","parent":"133","text":"Diffuse or patchy peritubular\\Ninflammatory cell infiltrates","guid":"kPymfJU7C4tmvxXhVe_ZUA","children":[{"id":"135","parent":"134","text":"T-cell lymphocytes","guid":"XoivUiRFa9tSSaBfETtpKw","children":[]},{"id":"136","parent":"134","text":"monocytes","guid":"YobyMIxyy1C3HAJ_twTZqQ","children":[{"id":"137","parent":"136","text":"macrophages, eosinophils,\\Nand plasma cells","guid":"YMCUuchVoFBic3l-4_Fa8g","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"138","parent":"133","text":"Interstitial edema","guid":"GEMfIbps0l1nE0qYVEqLzQ","children":[]},{"id":"139","parent":"133","text":"Sparing of glomeruli and vessels","guid":"u8NLwEYvgozFXEKwPr8Z-A","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"140","parent":"3","text":"\\\\*Differential\\Ndiagnoses\\\\*","guid":"sFPuIgXlqTZTbv9FpragRw","children":[{"id":"141","parent":"140","text":"Other causes of\\Nintrinsic AKI","guid":"7QSCZIhbkrYSCYUwLtXvAw","children":[{"id":"142","parent":"141","text":"Crystalline nephropathy","guid":"NABFWtZHVrJRwz0IOzOuGw","children":[]},{"id":"143","parent":"141","text":"Acute tubular necrosis","guid":"u6qRLwOrPoj2NeFQNPWwHQ","children":[]},{"id":"144","parent":"141","text":"Vasculitis","guid":"nGn5jdOVX977HWiyFqGNZQ","children":[]},{"id":"145","parent":"141","text":"Atheroembolic disease","guid":"H6zZLxy7UyWZDRKDKehKAg","children":[]},{"id":"146","parent":"141","text":"Glomerulonephritis","guid":"_D4GzctVI33lJsBoM4j9jQ","children":[]},{"id":"147","parent":"141","text":"DRESS syndrome","guid":"rt7xEChBhupFPl3pvppfYw","children":[]}]},{"id":"148","parent":"140","text":"Prerenal AKI","guid":"49uVDMvjMYSdVe0z-jMh3w","children":[]},{"id":"149","parent":"140","text":"Postrenal AKI","guid":"a_8vkLrEZHuxjNJICJnX1w","children":[]}]},{"id":"150","parent":"3","text":"\\\\*Management\\\\*","guid":"9JwTYClg901Oadkp9GN79A","children":[{"id":"151","parent":"150","text":"General","guid":"","children":[{"id":"152","parent":"151","text":"Stop causative agents or treat\\Nunderlying systemic disease.","guid":"XBo00_HJACPvfQuHU9GBCw","children":[]},{"id":"153","parent":"151","text":"Provide supportive care\\Nfor AKI for 3–5 days.","guid":"leUuqx8e-qny7MYVCOK44w","children":[{"id":"154","parent":"153","text":"avoid further renal insult and potentially aggravating\\Nfactors, support adequate kidney perfusion, and ensure\\Nearly identification and treatment of complications","guid":"--i80mnK_TcrBMc_0sEQ9A","children":[]}]},{"id":"155","parent":"151","text":"Consider systemic glucocorticoids\\Nunder specialist guidance","guid":"O9knfTW6G5t_XUFzpo4JDA","children":[]},{"id":"156","parent":"151","text":"Monitor kidney function; evaluate for\\Nindications for acute dialysis.","guid":"SytHZ-9xrqQZW7-cJohmgA","children":[]}]},{"id":"157","parent":"150","text":"\\\\*Glucocorticoid\\Ntherapy\\\\*","guid":"QyaPRezJ_pxo3xy-mR7NHw","children":[{"id":"158","parent":"157","text":"\\\\*Common\\Nindications\\\\*","guid":"2IUlJ5Z2tBJmrSYL0WEkhw","children":[{"id":"159","parent":"158","text":"Specific ATIN\\Netiologies","guid":"xYFiMafm2JYB6Nw_rwVLkw","children":[{"id":"160","parent":"159","text":"Drug-induced AIN","guid":"Z9ESV8aJavP_PWWiH232kg","children":[]},{"id":"161","parent":"159","text":"Autoimmune disorders","guid":"P6-Rmhr51N6ISH_iwUn2nA","children":[]},{"id":"162","parent":"159","text":"Postinfectious ATIN with\\Ndelayed recovery","guid":"8QTcTrVsUyqRM9GH3tTQEA","children":[]}]},{"id":"163","parent":"158","text":"Insufficient improvement in eGFR after 3–5\\Ndays of supportive care for AKI","guid":"oNAnbRIS3JUgJuBNIqI3Rg","children":[]},{"id":"164","parent":"158","text":"Impending indication for dialysis","guid":"viPMbsgGsFMIGajcLxKk9Q","children":[]},{"id":"165","parent":"158","text":"Diffuse infiltrates and no extensive\\Nfibrosis on biopsy sample","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"166","parent":"157","text":"\\\\*Example\\Nregimen\\\\*","guid":"JvdrVzQbccWZHNFgdosPow","children":[{"id":"167","parent":"166","text":"Methylprednisolone 250–500 mg IV\\Nonce daily for 3–4 days","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"168","parent":"166","text":"Seguido de Prednisone 0.5–1 mg/kg PO once daily\\Nfor 1–2 weeks, then taper off over 8–12 weeks.","guid":"TK50wdkgFXRTXUlMBjT2gw","children":[]}]},{"id":"169","parent":"157","text":"\\\\*Important\\Nconsiderations\\\\*","guid":"g76VV3vbMTqofyTWZZurmw","children":[{"id":"170","parent":"169","text":"There is a paucity of high-quality evidence to\\Nsupport the use of glucocorticoids in ATIN","guid":"lyRDxO8zpf0ikTSn0qzXkQ","children":[]},{"id":"171","parent":"169","text":"When indicated, glucocorticoids should\\Nbe started within 7 days of diagnosis.","guid":"mp5raOZ7HZW45LxypLj9mQ","children":[]},{"id":"172","parent":"169","text":"Consider stopping glucocorticoids if there is no\\Nimprovement in renal function after 1 week of therapy.","guid":"LehaqVGgaUhiygZD93Y2pQ","children":[]}]}]}]}]},{"id":"173","parent":"0","text":"Chronic tubulointerstitial\\Nnephritis","guid":"nNfdtcU9cfif2RVB5kN8aQ","children":[{"id":"174","parent":"173","text":"\\\\*Definition\\\\*","guid":"W9eE7a5CICF71flwNjer9g","children":[{"id":"175","parent":"174","text":"condition of chronic inflammation of the renal tubules and interstitium and\\Ncan progress to end-stage renal disease (ESRD) after mont